  	On June 2nd, Jin Zhiwei , Deputy Director of People&#39;s Government Foreign Affairs Office of Nantong, Jiangsu Province visit to New York.

  	The evening of June 2, the U.S. President of China-U.S. Chamber of Commerce Wynn Wang held a welcome banquet for the delegation. During the dinner, Jin Zhuren briefly describes the information of Nantong City. Nantong has a good quality of environmental population, known as &quot;China&#39;s first modern city&quot;; Nantong is just across the river to Shanghai, located south to the Jiangsu north plains, and connected by railway with Eurasia; through Yangtze River estuary, it can reach to the sea coastal and harbor in the rest of the world. Currently the GDP reached No. 8 within prefecture-level cities. It also describes the education, construction and textile industries development process, emphasizing the continued development of these industries are still dependent on the support of the majority of overseas Chinese.

  	For overseas Chinese investment in Nantong City, the government has a large number of service policies for oversea investors. Mr. Jin has grandly invited China-U.S. Chamber of Commerce member companies to go visit, hoping to attract and carry out overseas talent recruitment activities and actively introduced overseas well-known overseas Chinese communities to discuss cooperation in Nantong, invest and promote the city&#39;s enterprises to expand overseas business. President Wang affirmed the hope, the two sides made an agreement with the future of communication and cooperation.
